          <code code="29554-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Procedure description Narrative" />
          <title>Preoperative Diagnosis and Procedure</title>
          <text>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Date of Operation:</content> 09/28/2025
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Surgeon:</content> Dr. Marcus Rodriguez, MD, FACS
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Preoperative Diagnosis:</content>
              Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications (E11.9). Scheduled for
              minor office procedure: diabetic foot care and nail debridement.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Procedure Performed:</content>
              Debridement of diabetic foot lesion, right great toe. Nail trimming
              and callus debridement performed under sterile conditions.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Anesthesia:</content> Local, 1% lidocaine without epinephrine.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Estimated Blood Loss:</content> Minimal (&lt;5 mL).
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Specimens:</content> None.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Complications:</content> None.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Findings:</content>
              Thickened mycotic nails bilaterally. Hyperkeratotic lesion plantar surface right
              great toe approximately 1.2 cm diameter, grade 1 per Wagner classification.
              Adequate peripheral pulses palpable. No signs of active infection.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Postoperative Plan:</content>
              Wound care instructions provided. Follow-up in 2 weeks. Continue current
              diabetes management (metformin 1000 mg BID, lifestyle modification).
              HbA1c check ordered — last value 7.4% (03/2025).
            </paragraph>
          </text>
